App-Brl2Brl

This package contains the Perl module App::Brl2Brl and the command
line script brl2brl.

Version 0.03

Use case

Convert between braille character sets. If you for instance have
multiple braille printers with different characet set, you can use
this script to convert the data you want to print accordingly. The
respective display tables have to be present in a directory, and they
must have the format of Liblouis display tables (*.dis).


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc App::Brl2Brl
    perldoc brl2brl

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        https://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=App-Brl2Brl

    CPAN Ratings
        https://cpanratings.perl.org/d/App-Brl2Brl

    Search CPAN
        https://metacpan.org/release/App-Brl2Brl


